♫I love you♫

239
00:14:33,460 --> 00:14:34,620
I told you it was fun.

240
00:14:34,650 --> 00:14:35,910
You didn't believe me.

241
00:14:49,820 --> 00:14:50,740
Sorry.

242
00:14:51,340 --> 00:14:53,000
I... I didn't stand properly.

243
00:14:53,060 --> 00:14:53,780
It's OK.

244
00:15:05,980 --> 00:15:06,770
You smiled?

245
00:15:07,980 --> 00:15:09,140
You smiled?

246
00:15:09,340 --> 00:15:10,260
Get up.

247
00:15:15,220 --> 00:15:15,980
Look at this.

248
00:15:17,060 --> 00:15:18,190
Does it look like me?

249
00:15:23,980 --> 00:15:25,020
This is for you.

250
00:15:25,300 --> 00:15:27,900
You'll feel better when you see pretty things.

251
00:15:27,980 --> 00:15:29,340
Let me add some magic.

252
00:15:54,420 --> 00:15:56,780
Just say what you want to say.

253
00:15:59,020 --> 00:16:01,420
The stars tonight are beautiful.

254
00:16:09,500 --> 00:16:10,620
So what?

255
00:16:11,060 --> 00:16:12,460
It doesn't matter whether they are beautiful or not.

256
00:16:12,460 --> 00:16:15,300
They're all things that can't be touched.

257
00:16:15,780 --> 00:16:17,020
Not really.

258
00:16:17,420 --> 00:16:19,980
Although we can't touch them,

259
00:16:20,420 --> 00:16:22,660
the brilliance and beauty of them

260
00:16:22,980 --> 00:16:24,640
are worthy of our admiration.

261
00:16:27,610 --> 00:16:29,700
Well, Mr. Ji,

262
00:16:29,980 --> 00:16:32,180
don't mind what happened during the day.

263
00:16:32,180 --> 00:16:33,240
It was an accident.

264
00:16:33,380 --> 00:16:34,640
They don't deserve it.

265
00:16:35,170 --> 00:16:36,700
I didn't take it seriously.

266
00:16:38,500 --> 00:16:39,420
That's good.

267
00:16:41,740 --> 00:16:44,380
It sounds like I cared about it.

268
00:16:49,820 --> 00:16:50,700
Mr. Ji,

269
00:16:50,860 --> 00:16:52,190
can I ask you a question?

270
00:16:52,820 --> 00:16:54,680
Why do you have so many questions?

271
00:16:59,900 --> 00:17:00,460
Go ahead.

272
00:17:01,900 --> 00:17:03,780
I've been wanting to ask this question for a long time.

273
00:17:03,780 --> 00:17:05,859
Why do you always write tragedies?

274
00:17:06,220 --> 00:17:07,680
Is there a special reason?

275
00:17:07,940 --> 00:17:09,220
Tragedy is reality.

276
00:17:09,500 --> 00:17:10,619
I just ended the novels with reality.

277
00:17:10,619 --> 00:17:13,550
But you can't tar everybody with the same brush.

278
00:17:13,980 --> 00:17:14,780
In my opinion,

279
00:17:15,180 --> 00:17:17,109
if a couple really like each other,

280
00:17:17,220 --> 00:17:18,900
they should trust each other.

281
00:17:19,220 --> 00:17:21,220
No matter what conflicts and misunderstandings there are,

282
00:17:21,220 --> 00:17:22,220
all can be solved.

283
00:17:26,500 --> 00:17:29,660
There are many things in life that have nothing to do with misunderstandings

284
00:17:29,660 --> 00:17:30,720
or right and wrong.

285
00:17:31,700 --> 00:17:33,780
Even if the previous misunderstanding was solved,

286
00:17:33,780 --> 00:17:35,940
there are still obstacles of reality and interests.

